<subSubSection pageId="86" pageNumber="87" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="86.[151,1437,800,1079]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[151,274,837,863]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Archilestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,274,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Archilestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mainly a North American genus; nine species have been described. There are few species and few records in South America (Garrison 
<emphasis box="[565,623,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">et al.</emphasis>
2010). The genus was not expected to occur in 
<collectingCountry box="[1173,1268,873,899]" name="Ecuador" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, but recently a photograph of an 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[354,477,909,935]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Archilestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[354,477,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Archilestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species was taken in 
<collectingRegion box="[727,946,909,935]" country="Ecuador" name="Pichincha" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Pichincha Province</collectingRegion>
by Remco Hofland (
<figureCitation box="[1186,1272,909,936]" captionStart="FIGURE 46" captionStartId="87.[151,250,1568,1593]" captionTargetBox="[227,1361,561,1549]" captionTargetId="figure@87.[227,1361,561,1549]" captionTargetPageId="87" captionText="FIGURE 46. Archilestes sp. ECUADOR, Pichincha Province, Mashpi Road, edge of a pool of mud, (about 0.1953, -78.8653, 869m), 29 xii 2012; photo Remco Hofland." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3339976/files/figure.png" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
); no specimen was collected and therefore its specific identity is unknown. It is possible that the species is 
<taxonomicName box="[1204,1357,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Archilestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chocoanus">
<emphasis box="[1204,1357,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">A. chocoanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pérez- Gutiérrez (2012), recently described from 
<collectingCountry box="[630,743,981,1007]" name="Colombia" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, or it is an undescribed species. Pertinent references on identification are 
<bibRefCitation author="Gloyd, L. K." box="[300,454,1017,1043]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 3" refId="ref191672" refString="Gloyd, L. K. (1980) The taxonomic status of the genera Superlestes and Cyptolestes Williamson, 1921 (Odonata: Lestidae). Occasional Papers of the Museum of Zoology, University of Michigan, 694, 1 - 3." type="journal article" year="1980">Gloyd (1980)</bibRefCitation>
, De Marmels (1982), 
<bibRefCitation author="Garrison, R. W." box="[701,881,1017,1043]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref190173" refString="Garrison, R. W. (1982) Archilestes neblina, a new damselfly from Costa Rica, with comments on the variability of A. latialatus Donnelly (Odonata: Lestidae). Occasional Papers of the Museum of Zoology, University of Michigan, 702, 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1982">Garrison (1982)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Perez-Gutierrez, L." box="[935,1197,1017,1043]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="349 - 354" refId="ref198705" refString="Perez-Gutierrez, L. (2012) Archilestes chocoanus spec. nov., a new damselfly from Colombia (Odonata: Lestidae). Odonatologica, 41 (4), 349 - 354." type="journal article" year="2012">Pérez-Gutiérrez (2012)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[1208,1331,1017,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Archilestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1208,1331,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Archilestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
typically inhabit slow-flowing streams with vegetated, pooled areas.
</paragraph>
